.UPDATE...
Issued at 1016 AM PDT Mon Mar 16 2026

The forecast remains on track this morning with the long duration
Heat Advisory having gone into effect at 10AM PDT. This is the
earliest and first Heat Advisory that we`ve issued in March for
our office. While we continue to message the risks and compounding
impacts of a heat wave, we want to also recognize that this is
occurring during the week of most schools Spring Break. On top of
regular visitors to the coastline, we`ll have many more out of
town or first time visitors. Water temperatures are mostly still
in the 50s, cold water shock is a very real risk, so be careful
out there! Also, we`re keeping an eye on increasing southerly
swell that may necessitate a Beach Hazard Statement at some point
this week. Stay cool as cool as you can this week.

